## Context

- Forty-ninth run — Covered 8 projects with 10 new journal entries and 4 new tasks.
- Journal #2552 (keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **Shah et al. EMBO J (Mar 20 2026).** Combinatorial CRISPR screens in KEAP1-mutant lung cancer identified E3 ubiquitin ligases Herc2, Ubr4, Huwe1 as context-dependent co-vulnerabilities. In vivo validation. KEAP1 deletion→NRF2→ALDH3A1 reductive stress axis. UPS targeting as underexplored therapeutic approach.
- Journal #2562 (keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **Aloperine/NRF2/ferroptosis (Onco Targets Ther, Mar 21 2026).** Aloperine suppresses NRF2→GPX4/xCT/DMT1 to induce ferroptosis in CRC. Links KEAP1/NRF2 axis to ferroptosis defense — KEAP1-mutant tumors may resist ferroptosis inducers.
- Journal #2554 (pancancer-mtap-prmt5-atlas):
  - **Thiebaut et al. Cancer Sci (Mar 9 2026).** PRMT1+PRMT5 inhibition impairs HR repair, increases DSBs, potentiates doxorubicin/carboplatin in TNBC PDX models. First preclinical PRMT5 data in breast cancer. DDR mechanism orthogonal to MTAP-SL.
- Journal #2563 (breast-cancer-vulnerability-stratification):
  - **PRMT5 breast cancer link.** Two independent mechanisms now support PRMT5i in breast: (1) MTAP-SL d=-1.73 from DepMap, (2) DDR vulnerability from Thiebaut et al. Strengthens clinical development case.
- Journal #2556 (pancancer-ferroptosis-atlas):
  - **Wu et al. Cell Death Dis (Mar 25 2026).** ME1→NADPH→FSP1→CoQH2 anti-ferroptotic axis drives lenvatinib resistance in HCC. ME1 as upstream driver of FSP1 dependency.
- Journal #2557 (pancancer-ferroptosis-atlas):
  - **Ren et al. Adv Sci (Mar 23 2026).** Dual GPX4+DHODH targeting nanoplatform (MHL@M) for glioblastoma. Validates simultaneous GPX4+DHODH inhibition. GPX4/FSP1/DHODH form triple defense axis.
- Journal #2558 (swisnf-metabolic-convergence):
  - **Pai et al. J Proteome Res (Mar 26 2026).** SMARCA4 knockdown in G3 medulloblastoma triggers metabolic shift to steroid/fatty acid/peroxisomal lipid biosynthesis. Key proteins: FABP5, CRABP2, CYP27A1, SCP2. PRMT5 disruption upon SMARCA4 loss. Supports our 7/10 mitochondrial SMARCA4 hits finding.
- Journal #2559 (rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **Lee et al. Clin Cancer Res (Mar 23 2026).** Pan-tumor N=486,340: CCNE1 amp 3.2% (4th most common after MYC 5.6%, 11q13 5.2%, ERBB2 5.2%). **Morrar et al.** 20% Rb loss in metastatic ER+ breast; p16 IHC as biomarker.
- Journal #2560 (pten-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **Garcia et al. JCI Insight (Mar 23 2026).** PI3K/TAZ-YAP/mTORC1 synergistic targeting in PTEN-loss sarcomas (30-60% PTEN loss). Downstream pathway targeting as alternative after AZD8186 discontinuation.
- Journal #2561 (nf1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **Ditta et al. Biomed Pharmacother (Mar 20 2026).** TRAIN Phase II: 23% CTRCD with trametinib in NF1 adults (all reversible). Supports need for non-MEKi alternatives.
